1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,904
Modern cities host huge events every week - cricket, concerts, rallies.

2
00:00:05,954 --> 00:00:12,194
But traffic control is still reactive: we respond only after the jam forms.

3
00:00:12,244 --> 00:00:18,736
TraffiSense.ai changes that: a predictive, simulation-driven command platform.

4
00:00:18,786 --> 00:00:24,858
Built on 8,000+ real Bengaluru ASTraM incidents, with MapMyIndia mapping.

5
00:00:24,908 --> 00:00:27,681
Planning starts with an event.

6
00:00:27,731 --> 00:00:36,431
Pick a real venue - M. Chinnaswamy Stadium - 40,000 attendance, 7 PM Saturday, clear weather.

7
00:00:36,481 --> 00:00:45,557
One click predicts impact, simulates strategies, optimizes resources, and plans emergency routes.

8
00:00:45,607 --> 00:00:53,466
Here's the forecast: predicted congestion blooms across the CBD corridors.

9
00:00:53,516 --> 00:01:04,048
A gravity demand model fuses event load, historical incident density, and an ML closure-risk score.

10
00:01:04,098 --> 00:01:13,881
Every corridor is explained: 1,300 vehicles, 61% saturation, 19 min delay, 40% closure risk.

11
00:01:13,931 --> 00:01:22,807
Resource deployment - officers, barricades, marshals, tow trucks - allocated by marginal need.

12
00:01:22,857 --> 00:01:32,018
Mekhri Circle, a chronic hotspot with 64 incidents, gets the most officers: ~19% queue reduction.

13
00:01:32,068 --> 00:01:37,526
Every recommendation ships with a plain-English rationale.

14
00:01:37,576 --> 00:01:40,473
Divert, retime signals, or both?

15
00:01:40,523 --> 00:01:49,315
The scenario engine compares five strategies: travel time, queue, emergency response, emissions.

16
00:01:49,365 --> 00:01:58,341
Full optimization delivers a 30% cut in average travel time - a digital twin to test plans safely.

17
00:01:58,391 --> 00:02:07,517
Just ask. The command assistant answers natural-language what-ifs, live from the simulation.

18
00:02:07,567 --> 00:02:10,908
What happens if heavy rain begins?

19
00:02:10,958 --> 00:02:20,582
Worst corridor 61% to 100%, severe corridors 0 to 7, delay 15 to 59 min. Pre-position tow trucks.

20
00:02:20,632 --> 00:02:24,103
Under the hood: real machine learning.

21
00:02:24,153 --> 00:02:33,738
A RandomForest predicts road closures - an imbalanced 7% problem - with data leakage caught and removed.

22
00:02:33,788 --> 00:02:42,262
Honest holdout AUC 0.80, a 4.3x lift over the base rate, and stable 5-fold cross-validation.

23
00:02:42,312 --> 00:02:50,508
TraffiSense.ai - anticipate, test every plan, deploy with confidence. Proactive, at last.
